$interpreted: General: Listen, direct order from king Theodore! For the sake of the kingdom's people, we are chopping down this monstrous tree today for sure!
General: Charge!
Dagger: Not so fast——!

Dagger: If you don't like something, just destroy it...
Grrrrr, guess it ain't hard to be human leader!
Sione: That's not the case, which is why we chose to support princess Angelia.
Sione: You two, now it's the time you get inside!
General: Damnit! Stop those two children!
Sione: In your dreams!
Dagger: We drove them away, for now at least. How exhausting...
Sione: Sir Dagger and fellow Bear soldiers, thank you for the support.
Dagger: On a side note, did Angelia really think this through?
Dagger: Isn't it more beneficial for us to let Theodore's forces throw themselves at this weird tree until both suffered serious casualties?
Sione: I believe so. Besides, if we can cause public outrage among the capital's residents, it will only benefit the princess and her campaign.
Dagger: Yeah. But if that's case, why did Angelia ask us to come here? Just let Theodore do whatever he wants to this weird tree.
Sione: Princess will not sacrifice the capital's people just to gain an advantage for herself.
Sione: In addition... according to princess, she said she owes Theodore an apology. This tree incident will be her atonement.
Dagger: Apology? Why should Angelia say sorry to Theodore?
Sione: I don't exactly know the details either...
Alice: ... It's Deemo's piano music.
Masked Girl: Hmph, we will find him in no time.

Alice: The music... it's getting closer.
Deemo must be just ahead!
Puggi: Nope~ It's bedtime for the good kids. Puggi says, night night~
Masked Girl: I don't have time to screw around with you people! Get out of my way!
Puggi: Can't do. We're super~ serious, so serious that we can't get any more serious. We can't allow you to come closer.

Pang: This is not our intentions, but since we accepted the request, we shall do our best to fulfill it.
Apologies in advance.
Puggi: Yippee, we're done! I am awesome!
Puggi: Now that we're done with the mission, I finally get to hit on girls~ Cutie-pies, what are your names...
Puggi: Pang! Whaddaya doing! Stop getting in my way while I'm flirting!
Pang: Ignore this fat bird. The person you are looking for is right ahead. He is trapped by a bizarre monstrosity. We couldn't get near him.
Pang: However, if it's you two, perhaps you have what it takes to save him.
Alice: ... You guys were going easy on us back there?

Pang: When Puggi and I were sucked into this big tree,
it was your companion who protected us.
Pang: Even though we couldn't understand each other's languages, he is now a dear friend of mine.
Masked Girl: Then why did you guys...
Pang: He doesn't want you two to risk your lives to rescue him; hence why he asked Puggi and I to intercept you on your path.
Puggi: BUT~ Since we lost, we can't do anything about it now~
Puggi: Last challenge left. Get moving, cute girls~
Masked Girl: ... Such painful music. I feel suffocated just by listening to it...
Alice: Deemo!
Puggi: Don't forget to say goodbye! Hope to see ya girls again someday!
Puggi: Bye-bye, puggi puggi!
General: ... We've confirmed that all monsters attracted to the tree have been eliminated. We have yet to discover any similar incidents since then.
General: We believe it's safe to assume that said tree has completely vanished from within the borders of the kingdom.
Theodore: What about the army Angelia deployed?
General: They've retreated back to Totemtaff. As of now, no further actions are observed.
Theodore: ... Understood. Leave.
Ralph: Your Majesty Theodore...

Theodore: Huh...
Haha... Hahahaha!
Theodore: So Angelia is the one who cleaned up the mess for me this time...
Theodore: ... Naive child! I'm in the right! I will definitely not entrust the kingdom to her!
Theodore: Ralph, your investigation of the Bayer family, any progress?
Ralph: Yes. Just as your Majesty has predicted. The Bayers were preparing to betray us. They've already met with the princess in private.
Theodore: Then? I'm certain that you've already dealt with them?

Ralph: Please rest assured, your Majesty.
I have dealt with them cleanly and swiftly. Not a single survivor.
Theodore: ... Very well.
Theodore: ... Those without wings should never have the delusion of flying. Angelia, you will notice sooner than later, your own shortcomings.
Theodore: Let's go. I have to attend the military meeting.
